The registration has kicked off for the seventh edition of Miss Comely Queen Nigeria 2020, a pageant platform to raise beauty queens who will lead a campaign against breast cancer among women in the country. A statement signed by the president Comely Nation, Amb. Raymond Jefferson, and made available to LEADERSHIP yesterday in Abuja said, Miss Comely Queen Nigeria beauty pageant collaborates with both National and International organizations to create awareness on the causes, prevention and early signs of breast cancer. Jefferson said Comely Queens have been instrumental to a good number of successful breast cancer sensitization awareness projects across four major countries in West Africa especially in Nigeria since inception 2014. He noted that Miss Comely Queen Nigeria is ranked among the top 10 pageants in Nigeria and among the top 15 pageants in Africa. The statement reads in part: “Miss Comely Queen Nigeria was nominated for an international award at Nebraska, US in 2014, received both National and International recognition, hosted the highest number of pageant contestants in one of the most influential hotels in Abuja, championed 28 breast cancer awareness campaign in Nigeria, produceed a blockbuster movie on breast cancer “Pink Ribbon” and produced over 351 certified breast cancer awareness ambassadors. He said that the registration can be done on the Miss Comely Queen Nigeria website comelynation.org adding that the registration is free.